Photo: Michael Ochs /Archives/Getty ImagesMiriam Makeba’s grandson Lumumba Lee said the family was devastated.“The last time I spoke to him he sounded energetic and positive. He was always that man who didn’t give up. He was a fighter,” he said.In October, Masekela was supposed to perform at the Hugh Masekela Heritage Festival in Rockville, Soweto to dedicate himself to battling the disease and calling on men to go for regular cancer check-ups. But he cancelled the show because of poor health.